    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="996"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d996">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 703.4112/5.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <p>His Majesty’s Embassy has the honour to inform the State Department that in
                    compliance with their request Sir Edward Grey <pb facs="0759" n="643"
                        xml:id="pg_643"/> has directed Sir Lionel Garden to instruct the British
                    Consular officers at Frontera, La Paz, Ensenada, Colima, Salina Cruz and
                    Acapulco to take charge of American interests in the absence of French Consular
                    officers in those places.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 28, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
